msgctxt "84_Businessman"
msgid "See this spot over here? I heard it's like a local hub\r\n"
"for foreigners."
msgstr "See this spot over here? I heard it's like a local hub\r\n"
"for foreigners."

msgctxt "96_Businessman's Girlfriend"
msgid "Foreigners? Really? Like those guys from the\r\n"
"movies? Big Hollywood stars?"
msgstr "Foreigners? Really? Like those guys from the\r\n"
"movies? Big Hollywood stars?"

msgctxt "108_Businessman"
msgid "Nope, think a little more... eastward. I'm talking\r\n"
"immigrants from other Asian countries."
msgstr "Nope, think a little more... eastward. I'm talking\r\n"
"immigrants from other Asian countries."

msgctxt "120_Businessman's Girlfriend"
msgid "Oh, wow... I bet I'd walk in the room and have no idea\r\n"
"what anybody's saying."
msgstr "Oh, wow... I bet I'd walk in the room and have no idea\r\n"
"what anybody's saying."

msgctxt "132_Businessman"
msgid "Yeah, but I'm sure you'd understand their cooking.\r\n"
"Good food's like an international language. I'd love\r\n"
"to try this place out, but I don't know how to get in."
msgstr "Yeah, but I'm sure you'd understand their cooking.\r\n"
"Good food's like an international language. I'd love\r\n"
"to try this place out, but I don't know how to get in."

msgctxt "144_Businessman's Girlfriend"
msgid "Can't you enter from where that guy's always standing?\r\n"
"Wonder why he's not there now..."
msgstr "Can't you enter from where that guy's always standing?\r\n"
"Wonder why he's not there now..."

msgctxt "156_Businessman"
msgid "Hey, you're right. Still, you don't know what to expect\r\n"
"around here. I bet no one even speaks Japanese."
msgstr "Hey, you're right. Still, you don't know what to expect\r\n"
"around here. I bet no one even speaks Japanese."

